The paper discusses data analysis methods that aim to uncover the underlying low dimensional structure imposed by the low dimensional hidden parameters. This is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of "dimensionality reduction". The paper proposes a method that utilizes multiple views of the data to extract valuable geometric information. This falls under the category of "multi-view learning". Therefore, the most likely sub-category is "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence), "cs.CV" (Computer Vision), "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms), and "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks).
